cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on techniques to improve program comprehension, which is a key aspect of software engineering. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with source code and its abstract nature. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses techniques to improve the user experience of developers working with source code. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques in some of the evaluations. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with techniques to make source code more "sound" and understandable.
